---
import { Picture } from "astro:assets";
import portrait from "../assets/img/Logic Woods 3.webp";
---

<section class="py-24 bg-secondary-500 text-primary-900" id="about">
  <div class="w-[min(1200px,90vw)] mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr,0.9fr] gap-12 items-start">
    <div>
      <div class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.25em] uppercase text-accent-700" data-aos="fade-up">About</div>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-[clamp(22px,3.2vw,30px)] font-bold leading-tight" id="headline-about" data-aos="fade-up">
        About
      </h2>
      <div class="text-start text-base text-primary-700 leading-relaxed space-y-6" data-aos="fade-up">
        <p>
            Tobias Lorsbach is a Mainz, Germany-based artist known as <span
              class="artist-name">Logic Moon</span
            >. His previous releases have appeared on internationally recognized
            labels such as Whitelabrecs, Archives, Archipel, DRONARIVM,
            Ambientologist, Shimmering Moods, and his own Logic Moon Music
            imprint across both physical and digital formats. He spent many
            years in the minimal techno scenes since the early 2000s, and whilst
            out on a field recording excursion, he fell upon the idea of
            layering some ambient drones. From here, his debut album as <span
              class="artist-name">Logic Moon</span
            > was born - "Herbst11".
          </p>

          <p>
            Tobias' musical background has drawn in a widescreen of genres, with
            him having performed guitar in a death metal band, embarked on a DJ
            career, and now established himself as an ambient musician. His
            varied experiences have only served to give birth to a range of
            ideas which are evident in his acclaimed albums, including "I See
            Planets" (2019) and his most recent release "Music For Film Vol.1"
            (2024), alongside numerous collaborative works.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-secondary-100 border border-secondary-200/60 rounded-md p-4 text-primary-800">
            Logic Moon has become well known for his mastering and
            post-production work for internationally recognized labels like
            Whitelabrecs, DRONARIVM, Archives, and many artists all over the
            globe.
          </div>

          <p>
            Recent collaborative projects include works with Swedish cellist
            Henrik Meierkord on albums such as "Inseln" (2022) and "Ewiger
            Wald" (2024), as well as partnerships with artists like Sven Laux
            and Scarless Arms, showcasing his ability to seamlessly blend
            classical instrumentation with electronic soundscapes.
          </p>

          <p>
            Logic Moon's style is frequently regarded as lively and
            emotionally engaging, with his compositions striking a delicate
            balance between classical accessibility and adventurous
            exploration. His work spans from cinematic ambient pieces to deep
            drone compositions, often incorporating field recordings and
            creating atmospheric journeys that transport listeners to
            otherworldly realms.
          </p>

          <div class="flex gap-4 mt-4 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent-700">
            <a href="/logic-moon-bio" class="hover:text-accent-600" title="Logic Moon biographical info">Biographical Info</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    <div class="bg-secondary-100 border border-secondary-200/60 rounded-lg p-3">
      <Picture
        src={portrait}
        alt="portrait"
        widths={[400, 800, 1200]}
        sizes={"(min-width: 768px) 34vw, 50vw"}
        formats={["avif", "webp"]}
        class="hidden sm:block w-full rounded-md"
        data-aos="fade-up"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

</section>
